pull.title: Add const to methods that do not modify the object for which it is called

events.body: `isRestartRequired()` in `optionsmodel.(h|cpp)` can also be made const, I think.
utACK 17d6213f1ed08ce9907b90d22cc9596267eeeb73 (but if it compiles everything is correct, it is true that only adds const to methods that look like should be const).
Adding link to ["By default, make member functions `const`" (Con.2)](https://github.com/isocpp/CppCoreGuidelines/blob/master/CppCoreGuidelines.md#Rconst-fct) in the C++ Core Guidelines.

issue.title: Denote functions CNode::GetRecvVersion() and CNode::GetRefCount()  as const
issue.body:
CNode::GetRecvVersion() is now denoted as const
 CNode::GetRefCount() is also now denoted as const, after a PR comment
